      "blocks": {
        "p_1": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Each Studio Unto Color Gem is produced with natural materials such as burnt chalk, apple, stones and granite.</p>"
          }
        },
        "p_2": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Using the Color Gems is a process similar to rock erosion: every line you draw and every indentation you press into it slowly transforms the crayon cube, turning the natural process of erosion into an artistic footprint.</p>"
          }
        },
        "p_3": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The original cube shape invites the user to determine the “rock form” through the act of drawing; every sign of press, indent and dulled corner implies the artistic footprints.</p>"
          }
        },
        "p_4": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>All Color Gems are handmade in Unto’s studio in Taipei, and therefore they all have slightly different colors and irregularities.</p>"
          }
        },
